<HTMLOptionElementText>
<summary>
The <strong><c>text</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLOptionElement"/> represents the text inside the {{htmlelement("option")}} element.<br/>This property represents the same information as <see cref="Node.TextContent"/>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<blockquote><para>If the element has a <c>label</c>, the text inside the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/option">option</see> is not visually rendered. In this case, the <c>text</c> property can still be used to set the content, but it will have no visible effect.</para></blockquote>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select">select</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/datalist">datalist</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/optgroup">optgroup</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLOptionElement.Value"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLOptionElement.Label"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLScriptElement.Text"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLAnchorElement.Text"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLOptionElement/text"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
</HTMLOptionElementText>
